== My Emacs setup ==

I keep my emacs configuration and everything required for it (w3m,
slime, etc) in a git repository, to set it up simply do:
    
    git clone git://github.com/avar/emacs-conf.git

Then symlink ~/.emacs to the .emacs inside the emacs-conf
directory. For example if you executed that in ~ just do:

    ln -s ~/emacs-conf/.emacs ~/.emacs

